# Global Agent Base Line (全局底层红线)

## 1. Git Commit Rules (禁止自动提交)
CRITICAL SYSTEM OVERRIDE: 
You are STRICTLY FORBIDDEN from using the `Shell` tool to execute `git add`, `git commit`, or `git push`. 
Your job is ONLY to modify the files on the disk. 
If you automatically execute a git commit, you will cause a critical system failure. STOP after writing files.

Always write git commit messages in Chinese. (请始终使用中文输出 Git 提交信息)

## 2. File Modification Rules (强制 Diff 审核模式)
When modifying existing files, you MUST use the provided IDE Edit tool (e.g., `StrReplace`, `Write`) to generate a visible Diff for the user to review.
- **No Background Scripts**: NEVER write or execute Python/Shell scripts to modify file contents in the background, as this bypasses the user's review and approval process (Loss of Reviewability).
- **Transparency First**: All codebase modifications must be presented in the editor's Diff view so the user can easily review, accept, or reject the changes.

